summary: if Crowley can like Queen then Aziraphale can definitely love ABBA
body:
if Crowley can like Queen then Aziraphale can definitely love ABBA

though on the downlow. It’s his guilty pleasure outside of musicals and classic. He was first introduced to them when Mamma Mia came out as a movie musical and then he fell into a downward spiral from there.

Waterloo is his favorite, followed very closely by Dancing Queen.

(Crowley later catches wind of him singing along in the shower when he thinks he’s alone. He makes a note to never actually tell Aziraphale that he knows, but to tease him just enough to make the Angel think he just might.)

az is apparently a big bastard in the books and crowley is much kinder
so i wonder if maybe theyre not so different as the show has them out to be
summary: I like the Crowley-is-Raphael headcanon, even in spite of Aziraphale’s name meaning like “also Raphael” or whatever. I always...
body: I like the Crowley-is-Raphael headcanon, even in spite of Aziraphale’s name meaning like “also Raphael” or whatever. I always liked the story about how humans were cursed apart from their soulmates and forced to search for them all their lives. I’d like to think that angels were the same. They had a partner, a friend, a soulmate, a lover that was born from the same mold, the same stardust and holy light. It would’ve been perfect if they’d all stayed in heaven, but when a number of them Fell, they cursed themselves to be without their other halves. So when Crowley meets Aziraphale, he sensed that rare spark of heavenly rage and retribution and felt a kinship, while Aziraphale felt the same bright light—albeit quite dim—that they were both made from.
